
[1]succinct

   SUCCINCT', a. ]L. succinctus; sub and cingo, to surround.]

   1. Tucked up; girded up; drawn up to permit the legs to be free.

   Hib habit fit for speed succinct. [Little used.]

   2. Compressed into a narrow compass; short; brief; concise; as a
   succinct account of the proceedings of the council.

   Let all your precepts be succinct and clear.
